<h2 id="flow-actions">Flow Actions</h2>

<p>Three invocable actions for Salesforce Flow — use in Record-Triggered Flows, Screen Flows, Scheduled Flows, and Subflows:</p>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Generate Document</h3>
    <p><strong>Input:</strong> Template ID, Record ID &nbsp; <strong>Output:</strong> Content Document ID</p>
    <p>Generates a single document synchronously. Use for automating document creation on record events — for example, auto-generate a welcome PDF when a new Contact is created.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Generate Bulk Documents</h3>
    <p><strong>Input:</strong> Template ID, WHERE Condition, Batch Size &nbsp; <strong>Output:</strong> Job ID</p>
    <p>Launches async batch generation. Returns a Job ID to poll for completion. Use in Scheduled Flows for recurring document generation (monthly invoices, quarterly reports).</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
    <h3>Giant Query Auto-Detect</h3>
    <p><strong>Input:</strong> Template ID, Record ID &nbsp; <strong>Output:</strong> Content Doc ID or Job ID</p>
    <p>Auto-detects dataset size. Under 2K rows: generates sync. Over 2K: launches async batch. Ideal for Experience Cloud portals where dataset size is unknown — the user clicks one button and DocGen handles the rest.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="apex-api">Apex API Reference</h2>

<p>Call DocGen from your own Apex code, triggers, scheduled jobs, or Lightning components. All classes are global in the managed package namespace <code>portwoodglobal</code>, so you'll prefix them as <code>portwoodglobal.DocGenService</code> from subscriber code.</p>

<p><strong>Backwards compatibility:</strong> the APIs below are published as stable global methods. New optional overloads may be added in future releases; existing signatures will not be removed without a major version bump and deprecation notice.</p>

<h3>DocGenService &mdash; synchronous generation</h3>

<p>Primary entry point for generating documents from Apex. Use when you need to trigger DocGen programmatically from a trigger, scheduled Apex, or another service class.</p>

<table>
    <tr><th>Method</th><th>Returns</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generateDocument(Id templateId, Id recordId)</code></td><td><code>Id</code> (ContentDocumentId)</td><td>Generates a document, saves as a File on the record, returns the new ContentDocumentId. Uses the template's default output format.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generateDocument(Id templateId, Id recordId, String outputFormatOverride)</code></td><td><code>Id</code></td><td>Same as above but lets you pass <code>'PDF'</code>, <code>'Word'</code>, <code>'PowerPoint'</code>, or <code>'HTML'</code> to override the template's setting. Throws if the template locks output or if you ask for an incompatible format.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generatePdfBlob(Id templateId, Id recordId)</code></td><td><code>Map&lt;String, Object&gt;</code> with keys <code>blob</code> (PDF Blob), <code>title</code> (String)</td><td>Renders a PDF in-memory without saving it anywhere. Use when you want to email the PDF, attach it to a different record, or post it somewhere.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generateDocumentFromData(Id templateId, Id recordId, Map&lt;String, Object&gt; preloadedRecordData)</code></td><td><code>Id</code></td><td>Same as generateDocument but uses pre-fetched data instead of querying. Internal batch use; call directly if you're implementing your own bulk loop.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>renderPreviewHtml(Id templateId, Id recordId)</code></td><td><code>String</code> (HTML)</td><td>Returns the merged HTML that would go into Blob.toPdf. Useful for preview panes, email body, or custom rendering.</td></tr>
</table>

<pre style="background:#f4f6f9;padding:0.75rem;border-radius:4px;"><code>// Example: trigger PDF generation from an approval process
Id contentDocId = portwoodglobal.DocGenService.generateDocument(
    'a0zXXXXXXXXXXXXX',   // template ID
    accountId,            // record ID
    'PDF'                 // force PDF regardless of template setting
);</code></pre>

<h3>DocGenController &mdash; LWC / Aura endpoints</h3>

<p>Every method is <code>@AuraEnabled</code> so you can call them from your own Lightning web components, Aura components, or REST proxies. Use the <code>@salesforce/apex/portwoodglobal.DocGenController.*</code> import syntax from LWC.</p>

<table>
    <tr><th>Method</th><th>Returns</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generatePdf(Id templateId, Id recordId, Boolean saveToRecord)</code></td><td><code>Map&lt;String, Object&gt;</code> with <code>base64</code>, <code>contentDocumentId</code>, <code>title</code></td><td>LWC-friendly PDF generation. Set <code>saveToRecord=true</code> to attach, <code>false</code> to download client-side only.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generatePdfAsync(Id templateId, Id recordId)</code></td><td><code>Id</code> (AsyncApexJob Id)</td><td>Enqueues a Queueable to render + save. Use for large PDFs (over ~15 MB) that exceed the synchronous Aura timeout. Client polls for completion.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>generateDocumentGiantQuery(Id templateId, Id recordId)</code></td><td><code>Map&lt;String, Object&gt;</code> with <code>isGiantQuery</code>, <code>jobId</code> OR <code>docId</code> + <code>contentVersionId</code></td><td>Auto-routes: small child counts render synchronously, &gt; 2000 rows spawn a batched Giant Query job. Use when you don't know the dataset size in advance.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>saveTemplate(Map&lt;String, Object&gt; fields, Boolean createVersion, String contentVersionId)</code></td><td><code>void</code></td><td>Programmatic template save. <code>fields</code> includes Id, Name, Type__c, Base_Object_API__c, Query_Config__c, Header_Html__c, Footer_Html__c, etc. Pass <code>createVersion=true</code> and an uploaded <code>contentVersionId</code> to publish a new template version.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>getAllTemplates()</code></td><td><code>List&lt;DocGen_Template__c&gt;</code></td><td>Returns every template in the org (cacheable). Filter client-side.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>getTemplatesForObject(String objectApiName)</code></td><td><code>List&lt;DocGen_Template__c&gt;</code></td><td>Audience-filtered template list for a given SObject. Applies <code>Required_Permission_Sets__c</code> and <code>Record_Filter__c</code> rules.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>getTemplatesForObjectAndRecord(String objectApiName, String recordId)</code></td><td><code>List&lt;DocGen_Template__c&gt;</code></td><td>Same as above plus per-record filter matching (checks <code>Specific_Record_Ids__c</code> and runtime <code>Record_Filter__c</code> evaluation).</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>saveHtmlTemplateImage(Id templateId, String fileName, String base64Content)</code></td><td><code>Map&lt;String, Object&gt;</code> with <code>contentVersionId</code>, <code>url</code></td><td>Stores an inline image from an HTML template upload (v1.61+). Called from the LWC during client-side unzip.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>saveHtmlTemplateBody(Id templateId, String fileName, String htmlContent)</code></td><td><code>Map&lt;String, Object&gt;</code> with <code>contentVersionId</code>, <code>contentDocumentId</code></td><td>Stores the rewritten HTML body after image extraction.</td></tr>
</table>

